    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Homework II: Directed Graphs\"\n---\n\n\n\n::: {.cell fig-cap-location='margin'}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![A directed graph.](homework2-answered_files/figure-html/fig-grex1-1.png){#fig-grex1 width=1152}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\nConsider the graph shown in @fig-grex1:\n\n\n1. Write down the **edge set** of the graph:\n<br>\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n`````{=html}\n<table>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> EA, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> IA, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> IB, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> JB, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> AC, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> GC, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> LC, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> ED, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> FD, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> AE, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> DE, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> HE, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> EF, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> LF, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> CG, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> FH, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> JH, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> LH, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> AI, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> GI, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> HI, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> GJ, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> KJ, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> AK, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> GK, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> LD, </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> LE, </td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n`````\n:::\n:::\n\n<br>\n\n## Directed Graph Neighborhoods\n\n1. Who are the **out-neighbors** of node *A*?\n<br>\nC, E, I, K\n<br>\n\n1. Who are the **in-neighbors** of node *E*?\n<br>\nA, D, H, L\n<br>\n\n1. What is the **intersection** of the **out-neighborhoods** of nodes *A* and *I*?